description.narrative: Discontinued. Merged with Output 1By 2022, the Ministry of Planning, Development and Reform endorses a comprehensive multi- sectoral CRVS strategy with clear modalities for embedding provincial birth registration data into the national system., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, 65 % of girls and boys under-5 are registered in Pakistan, with universal birth registration achieved and embedded within civil registration and vital statistics (CRVS) systems in two provinces, children access appropriate child protection preventive and/or response services, primarily through public case management and referral system in at least two provinces, and communities practice positive behaviours contributing towards a protective environment for children.

description.narrative: Strategic advocacy by UNICEF to Ministry of Planning, Development and Special Initiatives (MoPDSI) and provincial local government departments contributed toward the implementation of the Government of Pakistan’s commitment to the Regional Framework for Action for CRVS and budget allocation of USD 188 million across the provinces as well as reform of the CRVS rules and by-laws in KP, Sindh and Punjab to address gaps in existing legislation and promote inclusiveness. Joint effort by UNICEF, UNHCR and UNESCAP informed the pilot of CRVS model district in ICT to move birth notification from union councils to hospitals. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/01/2021
